### The risks of travelling without proper travel insurance cover
Insurers will require disclosure of pre-existing medical conditions of all
those people to be insured on the policy. Many standard travel policies will
exclude any pre-existing medical conditions. This means that if you had to
make a claim for medical emergency treatment costs for any pre-existing
conditions, or any related complications whilst away, some insurers may not
You should also be aware that other people travelling with you, who may be
covered under a different provider’s policy, may not be covered for
cancellation of the trip if it is cancelled due to your medical circumstances.
AllClear Insure My Diabetes offer travelling companion cancellation cover as a
The EHIC allows you to access state-provided healthcare in all European
There are restrictions on the cover provided via the EHIC and as a result, is
not a comprehensive alternative to travel insurance. EHIC is not valid on
European cruises, does not cover private healthcare, costs such as mountain
rescue, being repatriated back to the UK, and stolen property.
Full details of the cover provided by the EHIC can be found on the EHIC
